com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.auth

Class AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.auth.AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    AdobeAuthSessionLauncher

    public static class AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    The builder object used to construct an AdobeAuthSessionLauncher object.

    Example usage: authManager.login( new AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.Builder().withActivity(this).withRequestCode(DEFAULT_SIGN_IN_REQUEST_CODE).build());

    Note that User Auth UI can either be launched from an Activity or a Service. Both can not be used at the same time.

      • withContext

        public AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.Builder withContext(android.content.Context context)
        Provides the information regarding the context which is used to launch the user auth UI. Use this option to launch the user auth UI from a Service. When this option is used the results of the sign-in Activity can not be returned.
        Parameters:

        builder object for AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.

      • withRequestCode

        public AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.Builder withRequestCode(int requestCode)
        The request code used to launch the sign-in Activity. Note that the request code is used only in the case where an Activity is used to launch the user auth UI. If this option is not used, then a default request code will be used internally by SDK.
        Parameters:
        requestCode - request code used to launch the sign in Activity.
        Returns:
        builder object for AdobeAuthSessionLauncher.
